<subSubSection id="C36E651149190D26FF23BD99FE74FB27" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCB369A49190D26FF23BD99FE74FB27" blockId="5.[113,766,898,1274]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B900EA8849190D26FF23BD99FF4EFC44" box="[151,208,898,921]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D1949190D26FF40BD99FE40FC44" box="[244,478,898,922]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="montagnei">
<emphasis id="B900EA8849190D26FF40BD99FE40FC44" box="[244,478,898,922]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Plagiochila montagnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common neotropical rainforest species that is recognized by terminal branching and ovate-lingulate leaves with a longly decurrent dorsal base, toothed ventral and apical margins, and strongly ampliate ventral bases with triangular teeth (HEINRICHS &amp; GRADSTEIN, 2000). The species is common in lowland forests and is only occasionally seen in montane forests. The specimen 
<emphasis id="B900EA8849190D26FD3FBA59FD62FB87" box="[651,764,1090,1114]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Allioni 709</emphasis>
is chosen here as the 
<typeStatus id="54CF883849190D26FEE2BA79FE29FBA7" box="[342,439,1122,1146]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D1949190D26FE68BA79FDB9FBA4" box="[476,551,1122,1145]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="nova">
<emphasis id="B900EA8849190D26FE68BA79FDB9FBA4" box="[476,551,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">P.nova</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it was illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE54B6B49190D26FF39BA99FEA2FB44" author="STEPHANI, F." box="[141,316,1153,1178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="ref9306" refString="STEPHANI, F. (1985). Icones Hepaticarum. Microfiche edition. IDC, Zug." type="book" year="1985">STEPHANI (1985</bibRefCitation>
: tab. 11214). 
<collectionCode id="ED65AE5F49190D26FE0ABA99FE4CFB47" box="[446,466,1154,1178]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
